&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We Build Better Communities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Be Part of the Hawthorne Difference!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Hawthorne Cat is a family-owned company that has led its markets for over 60 years in the sale, rental, and servicing of construction machinery and power generation equipment for industries on which our communities depend like agriculture, construction, marine, and government.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Every member of our team plays a significant role in our success.&amp;nbsp; Hawthorne Cat hires individuals who share our vision of Building Better Communities with our Customers and our values of Passion, Respect, Integrity, Dedication and Excellence (PRIDE).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;If you are looking to build your future with an established, thriving company with countless opportunities for growth and advancement, you’ve come to the right place!&amp;nbsp; At Hawthorne Cat, we’re always looking for exceptionally skilled, hardworking individuals interested in contributing to our success and the success of the communities that we serve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Our people are our most valuable asset. That’s why at Hawthorne Cat we are committed to a comprehensive employee benefit program that helps our employees stay healthy, feel secure, and maintain a work/life balance.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POSITION SUMMARY:&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Under the supervision of the Service Manager, the Field Hydraulic Hose Technician is responsible for fabricating, assembling, and repairing hydraulic hoses and systems directly at customer sites and in the field. This role requires travel to various job locations to perform hose repairs, and hose replacement on equipment, while ensuring minimal downtime for customers. The Field Technician will have a strong understanding of hydraulic principles, hose specifications, and safety standards, and will serve as a front-line representative of Hawthorne Machinery Company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completes all job responsibilities in a safe manner, promotes and champions a safe and healthy work environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travels to customer sites in a fully equipped field service truck to provide on-site hydraulic hose service and support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fabricate hydraulic hoses according to specifications, including measuring, cutting, and crimping hoses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assemble and install hose fittings, ensuring proper connections and leak-free operation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspect and repair damaged hydraulic hoses and lines, determining the extent of the damage and the necessary repairs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot hydraulic system issues related to hoses and fittings in the field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform preventative maintenance on hydraulic hose assemblies and associated components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify hose specifications and select appropriate hoses and fittings for various applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible to maintain hose van inventory records, usage, and restocking orders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate records of field service calls, service reports, repairs, and installations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize Cat Interact and ServiceLink (computer programs) and other online tools as required.&lt;/li&gt;
